- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with caching optimization in heterogeneous networks with mutual interference and per-file rate constraints. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves optimization of caching allocation to minimize power consumption. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a low-complexity optimization algorithm. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with caching of files. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper involves coordination between multiple nodes.
